cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. Additionally, the use of semantic representations and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's focus on improving translation quality through the use of AMR (Abstract Meaning Representation) could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these fields often deal with improving the accuracy and relevance of search results through semantic analysis.
